OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FThe Foreign Secretary has warned that
OL,8,FIran's blockade of the Strait of
OL,9,FHormuz could result in tens of
OL,10,Fmillions going hungry as she told an
OL,11,Faid summit of the risk of
OL,12,F"sleepwalking into a global food
OL,13,Fcrisis".
OL,15,FYvette Cooper told an aid conference
OL,16,Fin London that the global south was
OL,17,Fpaying the highest price as the supply
OL,18,Fof fertiliser and heating oil remained
OL,19,Frestricted.
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FMarkets are already pricing in the
OL,8,Fdetrimental effect this will have on
OL,9,Ffarmers, and the World Food Programme
OL,10,Fhas estimated that 45 million people
OL,11,Fcould fall into acute food insecurity
OL,12,Fif the conflict does not end by the
OL,13,Fmiddle of the year.
OL,15,FThe Foreign Secretary said: "We meet
OL,16,Fagainst the backdrop of the Hormuz
OL,17,Fcrisis, a strait of water through
OL,18,Fwhich 90 ships a day used to pass, but
OL,19,Ffor the last three months it's been
OL,20,Fmore like five.
OL,26,@wD@]OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"Heating oil for Asia ` stuck in the
OL,8,FStrait, fertilisers for Africa ` stuck
OL,9,Fin the Strait, 20,000 seafarers, 800
OL,10,Fships ` just stuck in the Strait.
OL,12,F"The global economy is being held
OL,13,Fhostage, and the global south is
OL,14,Fpaying the biggest price."
OL,16,FThe Strait of Hormuz, between Iran and
OL,17,Fthe Arabian Peninsula, has been
OL,18,Feffectively closed since the US and
OL,19,FIsrael launched their campaign against
OL,20,FIran at the end of February.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUvD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FTehran's blockade of the vital
OL,8,Fshipping lane has sent oil prices
OL,9,Fspiralling, but has also shut off
OL,10,Faccess to some of the world's most
OL,11,Fsignificant fertiliser factories,
OL,12,Fthreatening to push food prices up as
OL,13,Fwell.
OL,15,FCooper warned the summit that the
OL,16,Fblockade was affecting planting season
OL,17,Ftoo, and that damage is already being
OL,18,Fdone that will hit crop yields and
OL,19,Fsend food prices up well into next
OL,20,Fyear.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"The world risks sleepwalking into a
OL,8,Fglobal food crisis, and we cannot risk
OL,9,Ftens of millions of people going
OL,10,Fhungry because Iran has hijacked an
OL,11,Finternational shipping lane," she said.
OL,13,FShe called for faster coordinated
OL,14,Faction from multilateral development
OL,15,Fbanks and specific support for
OL,16,Ffertiliser markets to alleviate the
OL,17,Fimpact of the strait's closure.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FThis is a critical time in the
OL,8,Fagriculture calendar, and Cooper
OL,9,Fwarned that if global partners do not
OL,10,Fget fertiliser moving, emergency
OL,11,Fshipments will be needed, not just
OL,12,Fexternal investment and technology.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,19,FThe International Chamber of Commerce
OL,20,F(ICC) said Cooper was right to sound
OL,21,Fthe alarm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FJohn Denton, ICC secretary general,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Fertiliser is a time-critical
OL,9,Finput: if shipments do not move from
OL,10,Fthe Persian Gulf soon, farmers will
OL,11,Fmiss application windows, crop yields
OL,12,Fwill be lower and food prices will
OL,13,Finevitably rise.
OL,15,F"Higher prices are already forcing
OL,16,Ffarmers to delay or cut fertiliser
OL,17,Fpurchases ` demand destruction that
OL,18,Fwill translate directly into weaker
OL,19,Fharvests.
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779264378
OL,3,CYvette Cooper: Hormuz blockade risks
OL,4,Csending world sleepwalking into food
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,F"At the same time, production outages
OL,8,Fand shortages of essential inputs risk
OL,9,Fleaving key nutrients unavailable in
OL,10,Fsufficient quantities ahead of major
OL,11,Fplanting seasons later this year and
OL,12,Finto next."
OL,14,FYvette Cooper was speaking at the
OL,15,FGlobal Partnerships Conference in
OL,16,FLondon, convened to set out a new
OL,17,Fapproach to development amid cuts to
OL,18,Foverseas aid budgets.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
